      "role": "user",
      "content": "but if originalism is \"subjective\" like you said, then isn't it basically just a cover for political bias? if you can just pick whatever historical fact helps your case, how can it really be a \"legitimate\" legal method? it feels more like a way to make political decisions look like they're just following the law.",
